Police in Delta State have killed three suspected armed robbers in a gun duel. They also arrested six at different locations and recovered six locally-made guns and cartridges, it was said. Police spokesman Bright Edafe yesterday said three suspects were apprehended on Eku-Abraka Road in Ethiope East council, while another three were arrested at Oleh Roundabout in Isoko South council. Two robbery suspects were equally shot dead in Benin City, the Edo State capital, yesterday.   Taming petrol scarcity menace     Onnoghenâ€™s ghost     10,000 Osun PDP members defect to APC   The Command said it received information in the early hours of Sunday that a gang of armed robbers had invaded a petrol station off Murtala Mohamed Way, Benin City, upon which a crack team and some vigilantes were mobilised to the scene. The armed robbers were reportedly trailed to a different location where they were allegedly carrying out a robbery attack. On sighting the team of security operatives, the robbers were said to have opened fire on them which led to a shootout. It was said that two of the suspects fell to the superior firepower of the security operatives while others escaped with bullet injuries.